{{Canada-nonfiction-writer-stub}}

In [[igneous petrology]] an '''intermediate composition''' refers to the chemical composition of a rock that has 52-63 [[wt%]] [[Silicon dioxide|SiO<sub>2</sub>]] being an intermediate between [[felsic]] and [[mafic]] compositions. Typical intermediate rocks include [[andesite]], [[dacite]] and [[trachyandesite]] among [[volcanic rocks]] and [[diorite]] and [[granodiorite]] among [[plutonic]] rocks.

